The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Aug. 9: The Centre today started a pension scheme unveiled in the budget for unorganised sector workers under which it will contribute Rs 1,000 annually, provided the beneficiary makes a matching contribution.          
	The Swavalamban Scheme  announced by finance minister Pranab Mukherjee in his budget speech this year  aims to bring 40 lakh such workers over four years starting this financial year.                   
	 New Delhi: The Commonwealth Games organising committee on Monday sacked suspended joint director-general T.S. Darbari for suspect handling of a Games contract. Darbari, said to be close to committee chairman Suresh Kalmadi, had allegedly hired a UK firm without due tendering process or any written contract and also overpaid it for sundry services. He was also grilled by the Enforcement Directorate.                  
	 New Delhi: The Supreme Court will hear the appeal of three CPM workers jailed for life by a Nadia court for the 1983 murder of a Congress worker. Bibhash Chandra Debnath, Sambhu Ghosh and Sadananda Mondal were convicted of the murder of Ajit Debnath, a Congress worker in August 1994.                                                                                                                                              
